271 bool isToken() const override { return Kind == k_Token; } 0
272 bool isReg() const override { return Kind == k_Register; } 0
273 bool isImm() const override { return Kind == k_Immediate; } 0
274 bool isMem() const override { return isMEMrr() || isMEMri(); } 0
275 bool isMEMrr() const { return Kind == k_MemoryReg; } 0
276 bool isMEMri() const { return Kind == k_MemoryImm; } 0
277 bool isMembarTag() const { return Kind == k_Immediate; } 0
278 bool isTailRelocSym() const { return Kind == k_Immediate; } 0
279 ----
280 bool isCallTarget() const { 0
281 if (!isImm()) 0
282 return false; 0
283 ----
284 if (const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast(Imm.Val)) 0
285 return CE->getValue() % 4 == 0; 0
286 ----
287 return true; 0
288 } ----
289 ----

291 if (!isImm()) 0
292 return false; 0
293 ----
294 if (const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast(Imm.Val)) 0

296 ----
297 return false; 0
298 } ----

366 void print(raw_ostream &OS) const override { 0
367 switch (Kind) { 0
368 case k_Token: OS << "Token: " << getToken() << "\n"; break; 0
369 case k_Register: OS << "Reg: #" << getReg() << "\n"; break; 0
370 case k_Immediate: OS << "Imm: " << getImm() << "\n"; break; 0
371 case k_MemoryReg: OS << "Mem: " << getMemBase() << "+" 0
372 << getMemOffsetReg() << "\n"; break; 0
373 case k_MemoryImm: assert(getMemOff() != nullptr); 0
374 OS << "Mem: " << getMemBase() 0
375 << "+" << *getMemOff() 0
376 << "\n"; break; 0
377 } ----
378 } 0

399 ----
400 void addExpr(MCInst &Inst, const MCExpr *Expr) const{ 0
401 // Add as immediate when possible. Null MCExpr = 0. ----
402 if (!Expr) 0
403 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(0)); 0
404 else if (const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast(Expr)) 0
405 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(CE->getValue())); 0
406 else ----
407 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createExpr(Expr)); 0
408 } 0

411 assert(N == 2 && "Invalid number of operands!"); 0
412 ----

414 ----
415 assert(getMemOffsetReg() != 0 && "Invalid offset"); 0
416 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(getMemOffsetReg())); 0
417 } 0

423 ----

425 addExpr(Inst, Expr); 0
426 } 0

444 static std::unique_ptr CreateToken(StringRef Str, SMLoc S) { 0
445 auto Op = std::make_unique(k_Token); 0
446 Op->Tok.Data = Str.data(); 0
447 Op->Tok.Length = Str.size(); 0
448 Op->StartLoc = S; 0
449 Op->EndLoc = S; 0
450 return Op; 0
451 } ----
452 ----
453 static std::unique_ptr CreateReg(unsigned RegNum, unsigned Kind, 0
454 SMLoc S, SMLoc E) { ----
455 auto Op = std::make_unique(k_Register); 0
456 Op->Reg.RegNum = RegNum; 0
457 Op->Reg.Kind = (SparcOperand::RegisterKind)Kind; 0
458 Op->StartLoc = S; 0
459 Op->EndLoc = E; 0
460 return Op; 0
461 } ----
462 ----
463 static std::unique_ptr CreateImm(const MCExpr *Val, SMLoc S, 0
464 SMLoc E) { ----
465 auto Op = std::make_unique(k_Immediate); 0
466 Op->Imm.Val = Val; 0
467 Op->StartLoc = S; 0
468 Op->EndLoc = E; 0
469 return Op; 0
470 } ----

472 static bool MorphToIntPairReg(SparcOperand &Op) { 0
473 unsigned Reg = Op.getReg(); 0
474 assert(Op.Reg.Kind == rk_IntReg); 0
475 unsigned regIdx = 32; 0
476 if (Reg >= Sparc::G0 && Reg <= Sparc::G7) 0
477 regIdx = Reg - Sparc::G0; 0
478 else if (Reg >= Sparc::O0 && Reg <= Sparc::O7) 0
479 regIdx = Reg - Sparc::O0 + 8; 0
480 else if (Reg >= Sparc::L0 && Reg <= Sparc::L7) 0
481 regIdx = Reg - Sparc::L0 + 16; 0
482 else if (Reg >= Sparc::I0 && Reg <= Sparc::I7) 0
483 regIdx = Reg - Sparc::I0 + 24; 0
484 if (regIdx % 2 || regIdx > 31) 0
485 return false; 0
486 Op.Reg.RegNum = IntPairRegs[regIdx / 2]; 0
487 Op.Reg.Kind = rk_IntPairReg; 0
488 return true; 0
489 } ----
490 ----
491 static bool MorphToDoubleReg(SparcOperand &Op) { 0
492 unsigned Reg = Op.getReg(); 0
493 assert(Op.Reg.Kind == rk_FloatReg); 0
494 unsigned regIdx = Reg - Sparc::F0; 0
495 if (regIdx % 2 || regIdx > 31) 0
496 return false; 0
497 Op.Reg.RegNum = DoubleRegs[regIdx / 2]; 0
498 Op.Reg.Kind = rk_DoubleReg; 0
499 return true; 0
500 } ----
501 ----
502 static bool MorphToQuadReg(SparcOperand &Op) { 0
503 unsigned Reg = Op.getReg(); 0
504 unsigned regIdx = 0; 0
505 switch (Op.Reg.Kind) { 0
506 default: llvm_unreachable("Unexpected register kind!"); 0
507 case rk_FloatReg: 0
508 regIdx = Reg - Sparc::F0; 0
509 if (regIdx % 4 || regIdx > 31) 0
510 return false; 0
511 Reg = QuadFPRegs[regIdx / 4]; 0
512 break; 0
513 case rk_DoubleReg: 0
514 regIdx = Reg - Sparc::D0; 0
515 if (regIdx % 2 || regIdx > 31) 0
516 return false; 0
517 Reg = QuadFPRegs[regIdx / 2]; 0
518 break; 0
519 } ----
520 Op.Reg.RegNum = Reg; 0
521 Op.Reg.Kind = rk_QuadReg; 0
522 return true; 0
523 } ----
524 ----
525 static bool MorphToCoprocPairReg(SparcOperand &Op) { 0
526 unsigned Reg = Op.getReg(); 0
527 assert(Op.Reg.Kind == rk_CoprocReg); 0
528 unsigned regIdx = 32; 0
529 if (Reg >= Sparc::C0 && Reg <= Sparc::C31) 0
530 regIdx = Reg - Sparc::C0; 0
531 if (regIdx % 2 || regIdx > 31) 0
532 return false; 0
533 Op.Reg.RegNum = CoprocPairRegs[regIdx / 2]; 0
534 Op.Reg.Kind = rk_CoprocPairReg; 0
535 return true; 0
536 } ----
537 ----
538 static std::unique_ptr ----
539 MorphToMEMrr(unsigned Base, std::unique_ptr Op) { 0
540 unsigned offsetReg = Op->getReg(); 0
541 Op->Kind = k_MemoryReg; 0
542 Op->Mem.Base = Base; 0
543 Op->Mem.OffsetReg = offsetReg; 0
544 Op->Mem.Off = nullptr; 0
545 return Op; 0
546 } ----
547 ----
548 static std::unique_ptr ----
549 CreateMEMr(unsigned Base, SMLoc S, SMLoc E) { 0
550 auto Op = std::make_unique(k_MemoryReg); 0
551 Op->Mem.Base = Base; 0
552 Op->Mem.OffsetReg = Sparc::G0; // always 0 0
553 Op->Mem.Off = nullptr; 0
554 Op->StartLoc = S; 0
555 Op->EndLoc = E; 0
556 return Op; 0
557 } ----
558 ----
559 static std::unique_ptr ----
560 MorphToMEMri(unsigned Base, std::unique_ptr Op) { 0
561 const MCExpr *Imm = Op->getImm(); 0
562 Op->Kind = k_MemoryImm; 0
563 Op->Mem.Base = Base; 0
564 Op->Mem.OffsetReg = 0; 0
565 Op->Mem.Off = Imm; 0
566 return Op; 0
567 } ----
568 }; ----

571 ----
572 bool SparcAsmParser::expandSET(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc, 0
573 SmallVectorImpl &Instructions) { ----
574 MCOperand MCRegOp = Inst.getOperand(0); 0
575 MCOperand MCValOp = Inst.getOperand(1); 0
576 assert(MCRegOp.isReg()); 0
577 assert(MCValOp.isImm() || MCValOp.isExpr()); 0
578 ----
579 // the imm operand can be either an expression or an immediate. ----
580 bool IsImm = Inst.getOperand(1).isImm(); 0
581 int64_t RawImmValue = IsImm ? MCValOp.getImm() : 0; 0
582 ----
583 // Allow either a signed or unsigned 32-bit immediate. ----
584 if (RawImmValue < -2147483648LL || RawImmValue > 4294967295LL) { 0
585 return Error(IDLoc, 0
586 "set: argument must be between -2147483648 and 4294967295"); 0
587 } ----
588 ----
589 // If the value was expressed as a large unsigned number, that's ok. ----
590 // We want to see if it "looks like" a small signed number. ----
591 int32_t ImmValue = RawImmValue; 0
592 // For 'set' you can't use 'or' with a negative operand on V9 because ----
593 // that would splat the sign bit across the upper half of the destination ----
594 // register, whereas 'set' is defined to zero the high 32 bits. ----
595 bool IsEffectivelyImm13 = ----
596 IsImm && ((is64Bit() ? 0 : -4096) <= ImmValue && ImmValue < 4096); 0
597 const MCExpr *ValExpr; ----
598 if (IsImm) 0
599 ValExpr = MCConstantExpr::create(ImmValue, getContext()); 0
600 else ----
601 ValExpr = MCValOp.getExpr(); 0
602 ----
603 MCOperand PrevReg = MCOperand::createReg(Sparc::G0); 0
604 ----
605 // If not just a signed imm13 value, then either we use a 'sethi' with a ----
606 // following 'or', or a 'sethi' by itself if there are no more 1 bits. ----
607 // In either case, start with the 'sethi'. ----
608 if (!IsEffectivelyImm13) { 0
609 MCInst TmpInst; 0
610 const MCExpr *Expr = adjustPICRelocation(SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_HI, ValExpr); 0
611 TmpInst.setLoc(IDLoc); 0
612 TmpInst.setOpcode(SP::SETHIi); 0
613 TmpInst.addOperand(MCRegOp); 0
614 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createExpr(Expr)); 0
615 Instructions.push_back(TmpInst); 0
616 PrevReg = MCRegOp; 0
617 } 0
618 ----
619 // The low bits require touching in 3 cases: ----
620 // * A non-immediate value will always require both instructions. ----
621 // * An effectively imm13 value needs only an 'or' instruction. ----
622 // * Otherwise, an immediate that is not effectively imm13 requires the ----
623 // 'or' only if bits remain after clearing the 22 bits that 'sethi' set. ----
624 // If the low bits are known zeros, there's nothing to do. ----
625 // In the second case, and only in that case, must we NOT clear ----
626 // bits of the immediate value via the %lo() assembler function. ----
627 // Note also, the 'or' instruction doesn't mind a large value in the case ----
628 // where the operand to 'set' was 0xFFFFFzzz - it does exactly what you mean. ----
629 if (!IsImm || IsEffectivelyImm13 || (ImmValue & 0x3ff)) { 0
630 MCInst TmpInst; 0
631 const MCExpr *Expr; ----
632 if (IsEffectivelyImm13) 0
633 Expr = ValExpr; 0
634 else ----
635 Expr = adjustPICRelocation(SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_LO, ValExpr); 0
636 TmpInst.setLoc(IDLoc); 0
637 TmpInst.setOpcode(SP::ORri); 0
638 TmpInst.addOperand(MCRegOp); 0
639 TmpInst.addOperand(PrevReg); 0
640 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createExpr(Expr)); 0
641 Instructions.push_back(TmpInst); 0
642 } 0
643 return false; 0
644 } ----
645 ----
646 bool SparcAsmParser::MatchAndEmitInstruction(SMLoc IDLoc, unsigned &Opcode, 0
647 OperandVector &Operands, ----
648 MCStreamer &Out, ----
649 uint64_t &ErrorInfo, ----
650 bool MatchingInlineAsm) { ----
651 MCInst Inst; 0
652 SmallVector Instructions; 0
653 unsigned MatchResult = MatchInstructionImpl(Operands, Inst, ErrorInfo, 0
654 MatchingInlineAsm); ----
655 switch (MatchResult) { 0
656 case Match_Success: { 0
657 switch (Inst.getOpcode()) { 0
658 default: 0
659 Inst.setLoc(IDLoc); 0
660 Instructions.push_back(Inst); 0
661 break; 0
662 case SP::SET: 0
663 if (expandSET(Inst, IDLoc, Instructions)) 0
664 return true; 0
665 break; 0
666 } ----
667 ----
668 for (const MCInst &I : Instructions) { 0
669 Out.emitInstruction(I, getSTI()); 0
670 } ----
671 return false; 0
672 } ----
673 ----
674 case Match_MissingFeature: 0
675 return Error(IDLoc, 0
676 "instruction requires a CPU feature not currently enabled"); 0
677 ----
678 case Match_InvalidOperand: { 0
679 SMLoc ErrorLoc = IDLoc; 0
680 if (ErrorInfo != ~0ULL) { 0
681 if (ErrorInfo >= Operands.size()) 0
682 return Error(IDLoc, "too few operands for instruction"); 0
683 ----
684 ErrorLoc = ((SparcOperand &)*Operands[ErrorInfo]).getStartLoc(); 0
685 if (ErrorLoc == SMLoc()) 0
686 ErrorLoc = IDLoc; 0
687 } ----
688 ----
689 return Error(ErrorLoc, "invalid operand for instruction"); 0
690 } ----
691 case Match_MnemonicFail: 0
692 return Error(IDLoc, "invalid instruction mnemonic"); 0
693 } ----
694 llvm_unreachable("Implement any new match types added!"); 0
695 } 0
696 ----
697 bool SparcAsmParser::parseRegister(MCRegister &RegNo, SMLoc &StartLoc, 0
698 SMLoc &EndLoc) { ----
699 if (tryParseRegister(RegNo, StartLoc, EndLoc) != MatchOperand_Success) 0
700 return Error(StartLoc, "invalid register name"); 0
701 return false; 0
702 } ----
703 ----
704 OperandMatchResultTy SparcAsmParser::tryParseRegister(MCRegister &RegNo, 0
705 SMLoc &StartLoc, ----
706 SMLoc &EndLoc) { ----
707 const AsmToken &Tok = Parser.getTok(); 0
708 StartLoc = Tok.getLoc(); 0
709 EndLoc = Tok.getEndLoc(); 0
710 RegNo = 0; 0
711 if (getLexer().getKind() != AsmToken::Percent) 0
712 return MatchOperand_NoMatch; 0
713 Parser.Lex(); 0
714 unsigned regKind = SparcOperand::rk_None; 0
715 if (matchRegisterName(Tok, RegNo, regKind)) { 0
716 Parser.Lex(); 0
717 return MatchOperand_Success; 0
718 } ----
719 ----
720 getLexer().UnLex(Tok); 0
721 return MatchOperand_NoMatch; 0
722 } ----
723 ----
724 static void applyMnemonicAliases(StringRef &Mnemonic, ----
725 const FeatureBitset &Features, ----
726 unsigned VariantID); ----
727 ----
728 bool SparcAsmParser::ParseInstruction(ParseInstructionInfo &Info, 0
729 StringRef Name, SMLoc NameLoc, ----
730 OperandVector &Operands) { ----
731 ----
732 // First operand in MCInst is instruction mnemonic. ----
733 Operands.push_back(SparcOperand::CreateToken(Name, NameLoc)); 0
734 ----
735 // apply mnemonic aliases, if any, so that we can parse operands correctly. ----
736 applyMnemonicAliases(Name, getAvailableFeatures(), 0); 0
737 ----
738 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) { 0
739 // Read the first operand. ----
740 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Comma)) { 0
741 if (parseBranchModifiers(Operands) != MatchOperand_Success) { 0
742 SMLoc Loc = getLexer().getLoc(); 0
743 return Error(Loc, "unexpected token"); 0
744 } ----
745 } ----
746 if (parseOperand(Operands, Name) != MatchOperand_Success) { 0
747 SMLoc Loc = getLexer().getLoc(); 0
748 return Error(Loc, "unexpected token"); 0
749 } ----
750 ----
751 while (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Comma) || getLexer().is(AsmToken::Plus)) { 0
752 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Plus)) { 0
753 // Plus tokens are significant in software_traps (p83, sparcv8.pdf). We must capture them. ----
754 Operands.push_back(SparcOperand::CreateToken("+", Parser.getTok().getLoc())); 0
755 } ----
756 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the comma or plus. 0
757 // Parse and remember the operand. ----
758 if (parseOperand(Operands, Name) != MatchOperand_Success) { 0
759 SMLoc Loc = getLexer().getLoc(); 0
760 return Error(Loc, "unexpected token"); 0
761 } ----
762 } ----
763 } ----
764 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) { 0
765 SMLoc Loc = getLexer().getLoc(); 0
766 return Error(Loc, "unexpected token"); 0
767 } ----
768 Parser.Lex(); // Consume the EndOfStatement. 0
769 return false; 0
770 } ----
771 ----
772 ParseStatus SparcAsmParser::parseDirective(AsmToken DirectiveID) { 0
773 StringRef IDVal = DirectiveID.getString(); 0
774 ----
775 if (IDVal == ".register") { 0
776 // For now, ignore .register directive. ----
777 Parser.eatToEndOfStatement(); 0
778 return ParseStatus::Success; 0
779 } ----
780 if (IDVal == ".proc") { 0
781 // For compatibility, ignore this directive. ----
782 // (It's supposed to be an "optimization" in the Sun assembler) ----
783 Parser.eatToEndOfStatement(); 0
784 return ParseStatus::Success; 0
785 } ----
786 ----
787 // Let the MC layer to handle other directives. ----
788 return ParseStatus::NoMatch; 0
789 } ----
790 ----
791 OperandMatchResultTy ----
792 SparcAsmParser::parseMEMOperand(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
793 SMLoc S, E; 0
794 ----
795 std::unique_ptr LHS; 0
796 if (parseSparcAsmOperand(LHS) != MatchOperand_Success) 0
797 return MatchOperand_NoMatch; 0
798 ----
799 // Single immediate operand ----
800 if (LHS->isImm()) { 0
801 Operands.push_back(SparcOperand::MorphToMEMri(Sparc::G0, std::move(LHS))); 0
802 return MatchOperand_Success; 0
803 } ----
804 ----
805 if (!LHS->isIntReg()) { 0
806 Error(LHS->getStartLoc(), "invalid register kind for this operand"); 0
807 return MatchOperand_ParseFail; 0
808 } ----
809 ----
810 AsmToken Tok = getLexer().getTok(); 0
811 // The plus token may be followed by a register or an immediate value, the ----
812 // minus one is always interpreted as sign for the immediate value ----
813 if (Tok.is(AsmToken::Plus) || Tok.is(AsmToken::Minus)) { 0
814 (void)Parser.parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::Plus); 0
815 ----
816 std::unique_ptr RHS; 0
817 if (parseSparcAsmOperand(RHS) != MatchOperand_Success) 0
818 return MatchOperand_NoMatch; 0
819 ----
820 if (RHS->isReg() && !RHS->isIntReg()) { 0
821 Error(RHS->getStartLoc(), "invalid register kind for this operand"); 0
822 return MatchOperand_ParseFail; 0
823 } ----
824 ----
825 Operands.push_back( 0
826 RHS->isImm() 0
827 ? SparcOperand::MorphToMEMri(LHS->getReg(), std::move(RHS)) 0
828 : SparcOperand::MorphToMEMrr(LHS->getReg(), std::move(RHS))); 0
829 ----
830 return MatchOperand_Success; 0
831 } 0
832 ----
833 Operands.push_back(SparcOperand::CreateMEMr(LHS->getReg(), S, E)); 0
834 return MatchOperand_Success; 0
835 } 0
836 ----
837 template ----
838 OperandMatchResultTy SparcAsmParser::parseShiftAmtImm(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
839 SMLoc S = Parser.getTok().getLoc(); 0
840 SMLoc E = SMLoc::getFromPointer(S.getPointer() - 1); 0
841 ----
842 // This is a register, not an immediate ----
843 if (getLexer().getKind() == AsmToken::Percent) 0
844 return MatchOperand_NoMatch; 0
845 ----
846 const MCExpr *Expr; ----
847 if (getParser().parseExpression(Expr)) 0
848 return MatchOperand_ParseFail; 0
849 ----
850 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast(Expr); 0
851 if (!CE) { 0
852 Error(S, "constant expression expected"); 0
853 return MatchOperand_ParseFail; 0
854 } ----
855 ----
856 if (!isUInt(CE->getValue())) { 0
857 Error(S, "immediate shift value out of range"); 0
858 return MatchOperand_ParseFail; 0
859 } ----
860 ----
861 Operands.push_back(SparcOperand::CreateImm(Expr, S, E)); 0
862 return MatchOperand_Success; 0
863 } ----
864 ----
865 template ----
866 OperandMatchResultTy ----
867 SparcAsmParser::parseTailRelocSym(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
868 SMLoc S = getLoc(); 0
869 SMLoc E = SMLoc::getFromPointer(S.getPointer() - 1); 0
870 ----
871 auto MatchesKind = [](SparcMCExpr::VariantKind VK) -> bool { 0
872 switch (Kind) { ----
873 case TailRelocKind::Load_GOT: ----
874 // Non-TLS relocations on ld (or ldx). ----
875 // ld [%rr + %rr], %rr, %rel(sym) ----
876 return VK == SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_GOTDATA_OP; 0
877 case TailRelocKind::Add_TLS: ----
878 // TLS relocations on add. ----
879 // add %rr, %rr, %rr, %rel(sym) ----
880 switch (VK) { 0
881 case SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_TLS_GD_ADD: 0
882 case SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_TLS_IE_ADD: ----
883 case SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_TLS_LDM_ADD: ----
884 case SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_TLS_LDO_ADD: ----
885 return true; 0
886 default: 0
887 return false; 0
888 } ----
889 case TailRelocKind::Load_TLS: ----
890 // TLS relocations on ld (or ldx). ----
891 // ld[x] %addr, %rr, %rel(sym) ----
892 switch (VK) { 0
893 case SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_TLS_IE_LD: 0
894 case SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_TLS_IE_LDX: ----
895 return true; 0
896 default: 0
897 return false; 0
898 } ----
899 case TailRelocKind::Call_TLS: ----
900 // TLS relocations on call. ----
901 // call sym, %rel(sym) ----
902 switch (VK) { 0
903 case SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_TLS_GD_CALL: 0
904 case SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_TLS_LDM_CALL: ----
905 return true; 0
906 default: 0
907 return false; 0
908 } ----
909 } ----
910 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled SparcAsmParser::TailRelocKind enum"); ----
911 }; ----
912 ----
913 if (getLexer().getKind() != AsmToken::Percent) { 0
914 Error(getLoc(), "expected '%' for operand modifier"); 0
915 return MatchOperand_ParseFail; 0
916 } ----
917 ----
918 const AsmToken Tok = Parser.getTok(); 0
919 getParser().Lex(); // Eat '%' 0
920 ----
921 if (getLexer().getKind() != AsmToken::Identifier) { 0
922 Error(getLoc(), "expected valid identifier for operand modifier"); 0
923 return MatchOperand_ParseFail; 0
924 } ----
925 ----
926 StringRef Name = getParser().getTok().getIdentifier(); 0
927 SparcMCExpr::VariantKind VK = SparcMCExpr::parseVariantKind(Name); 0
928 if (VK == SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_None) { 0
929 Error(getLoc(), "invalid operand modifier"); 0
930 return MatchOperand_ParseFail; 0
931 } ----
932 ----
933 if (!MatchesKind(VK)) { 0
934 // Did not match the specified set of relocation types, put '%' back. ----
935 getLexer().UnLex(Tok); 0
936 return MatchOperand_NoMatch; 0
937 } ----
938 ----
939 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the identifier. 0
940 if (getLexer().getKind() != AsmToken::LParen) { 0
941 Error(getLoc(), "expected '('"); 0
942 return MatchOperand_ParseFail; 0
943 } ----
944 ----
945 getParser().Lex(); // Eat '(' 0
946 const MCExpr *SubExpr; ----
947 if (getParser().parseParenExpression(SubExpr, E)) { 0
948 return MatchOperand_ParseFail; 0
949 } ----
950 ----
951 const MCExpr *Val = adjustPICRelocation(VK, SubExpr); 0
952 Operands.push_back(SparcOperand::CreateImm(Val, S, E)); 0
953 return MatchOperand_Success; 0
954 } 0
955 ----
956 OperandMatchResultTy SparcAsmParser::parseMembarTag(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
957 SMLoc S = Parser.getTok().getLoc(); 0
958 const MCExpr *EVal; ----
959 int64_t ImmVal = 0; 0
960 ----
961 std::unique_ptr Mask; 0
962 if (parseSparcAsmOperand(Mask) == MatchOperand_Success) { 0
963 if (!Mask->isImm() || !Mask->getImm()->evaluateAsAbsolute(ImmVal) || 0
964 ImmVal < 0 || ImmVal > 127) { 0
965 Error(S, "invalid membar mask number"); 0
966 return MatchOperand_ParseFail; 0
967 } ----
968 } ----
969 ----
970 while (getLexer().getKind() == AsmToken::Hash) { 0
971 SMLoc TagStart = getLexer().getLoc(); 0
972 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the '#'. 0
973 unsigned MaskVal = StringSwitch(Parser.getTok().getString()) 0
974 .Case("LoadLoad", 0x1) 0
975 .Case("StoreLoad", 0x2) 0
976 .Case("LoadStore", 0x4) 0
977 .Case("StoreStore", 0x8) 0
978 .Case("Lookaside", 0x10) 0
979 .Case("MemIssue", 0x20) 0
980 .Case("Sync", 0x40) 0
981 .Default(0); 0
982 ----
983 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the identifier token. 0
984 ----
985 if (!MaskVal) { 0
986 Error(TagStart, "unknown membar tag"); 0
987 return MatchOperand_ParseFail; 0
988 } ----
989 ----
990 ImmVal |= MaskVal; 0
991 ----
992 if (getLexer().getKind() == AsmToken::Pipe) 0
993 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the '|'. 0
994 } ----
995 ----
996 EVal = MCConstantExpr::create(ImmVal, getContext()); 0
997 SMLoc E = SMLoc::getFromPointer(Parser.getTok().getLoc().getPointer() - 1); 0
998 Operands.push_back(SparcOperand::CreateImm(EVal, S, E)); 0
999 return MatchOperand_Success; 0
1000 } 0
1001 ----
1002 OperandMatchResultTy SparcAsmParser::parseCallTarget(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
1003 SMLoc S = Parser.getTok().getLoc(); 0
1004 SMLoc E = SMLoc::getFromPointer(S.getPointer() - 1); 0
1005 ----
1006 switch (getLexer().getKind()) { 0
1007 default: 0
1008 return MatchOperand_NoMatch; 0
1009 case AsmToken::LParen: 0
1010 case AsmToken::Integer: ----
1011 case AsmToken::Identifier: ----
1012 case AsmToken::Dot: ----
1013 break; 0
1014 } ----
1015 ----
1016 const MCExpr *DestValue; ----
1017 if (getParser().parseExpression(DestValue)) 0
1018 return MatchOperand_NoMatch; 0
1019 ----
1020 bool IsPic = getContext().getObjectFileInfo()->isPositionIndependent(); 0
1021 SparcMCExpr::VariantKind Kind = 0
1022 IsPic ? SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_WPLT30 : SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_WDISP30; 0
1023 ----
1024 const MCExpr *DestExpr = SparcMCExpr::create(Kind, DestValue, getContext()); 0
1025 Operands.push_back(SparcOperand::CreateImm(DestExpr, S, E)); 0
1026 return MatchOperand_Success; 0
1027 } ----
1028 ----
1029 OperandMatchResultTy ----
1030 SparcAsmParser::parseOperand(OperandVector &Operands, StringRef Mnemonic) { 0
1031 ----
1032 OperandMatchResultTy ResTy = MatchOperandParserImpl(Operands, Mnemonic); 0
1033 ----
1034 // If there wasn't a custom match, try the generic matcher below. Otherwise, ----
1035 // there was a match, but an error occurred, in which case, just return that ----
1036 // the operand parsing failed. ----
1037 if (ResTy == MatchOperand_Success || ResTy == MatchOperand_ParseFail) 0
1038 return ResTy; 0
1039 ----
1040 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::LBrac)) { 0
1041 // Memory operand ----
1042 Operands.push_back(SparcOperand::CreateToken("[", 0
1043 Parser.getTok().getLoc())); 0
1044 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the [ 0
1045 ----
1046 if (Mnemonic == "cas" || Mnemonic == "casx" || Mnemonic == "casa") { 0
1047 SMLoc S = Parser.getTok().getLoc(); 0
1048 if (getLexer().getKind() != AsmToken::Percent) 0
1049 return MatchOperand_NoMatch; 0
1050 Parser.Lex(); // eat % 0
1051 ----
1052 MCRegister RegNo; 0
1053 unsigned RegKind; ----
1054 if (!matchRegisterName(Parser.getTok(), RegNo, RegKind)) 0
1055 return MatchOperand_NoMatch; 0
1056 ----
1057 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the identifier token. 0
1058 SMLoc E = SMLoc::getFromPointer(Parser.getTok().getLoc().getPointer()-1); 0
1059 Operands.push_back(SparcOperand::CreateReg(RegNo, RegKind, S, E)); 0
1060 ResTy = MatchOperand_Success; 0
1061 } else { ----
1062 ResTy = parseMEMOperand(Operands); 0
1063 } ----
1064 ----
1065 if (ResTy != MatchOperand_Success) 0
1066 return ResTy; 0
1067 ----
1068 if (!getLexer().is(AsmToken::RBrac)) 0
1069 return MatchOperand_ParseFail; 0
1070 ----
1071 Operands.push_back(SparcOperand::CreateToken("]", 0
1072 Parser.getTok().getLoc())); 0
1073 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the ] 0
1074 ----
1075 // Parse an optional address-space identifier after the address. ----
1076 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Integer)) { 0
1077 std::unique_ptr Op; 0
1078 ResTy = parseSparcAsmOperand(Op, false); 0
1079 if (ResTy != MatchOperand_Success || !Op) 0
1080 return MatchOperand_ParseFail; 0
1081 Operands.push_back(std::move(Op)); 0
1082 } 0
1083 return MatchOperand_Success; 0
1084 } ----
1085 ----
1086 std::unique_ptr Op; 0
1087 ----
1088 ResTy = parseSparcAsmOperand(Op, (Mnemonic == "call")); 0
1089 if (ResTy != MatchOperand_Success || !Op) 0
1090 return MatchOperand_ParseFail; 0
1091 ----
1092 // Push the parsed operand into the list of operands ----
1093 Operands.push_back(std::move(Op)); 0
1094 ----
1095 return MatchOperand_Success; 0
1096 } 0
1097 ----
1098 OperandMatchResultTy ----
1099 SparcAsmParser::parseSparcAsmOperand(std::unique_ptr &Op, 0
1100 bool isCall) { ----
1101 SMLoc S = Parser.getTok().getLoc(); 0
1102 SMLoc E = SMLoc::getFromPointer(Parser.getTok().getLoc().getPointer() - 1); 0
1103 const MCExpr *EVal; ----
1104 ----
1105 Op = nullptr; 0
1106 switch (getLexer().getKind()) { 0
1107 default: break; 0
1108 ----
1109 case AsmToken::Percent: { 0
1110 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the '%'. 0
1111 MCRegister RegNo; 0
1112 unsigned RegKind; ----
1113 if (matchRegisterName(Parser.getTok(), RegNo, RegKind)) { 0
1114 StringRef name = Parser.getTok().getString(); 0
1115 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the identifier token. 0
1116 E = SMLoc::getFromPointer(Parser.getTok().getLoc().getPointer() - 1); 0
1117 switch (RegNo) { 0
1118 default: 0
1119 Op = SparcOperand::CreateReg(RegNo, RegKind, S, E); 0
1120 break; 0
1121 case Sparc::PSR: 0
1122 Op = SparcOperand::CreateToken("%psr", S); 0
1123 break; 0
1124 case Sparc::FSR: 0
1125 Op = SparcOperand::CreateToken("%fsr", S); 0
1126 break; 0
1127 case Sparc::FQ: 0
1128 Op = SparcOperand::CreateToken("%fq", S); 0
1129 break; 0
1130 case Sparc::CPSR: 0
1131 Op = SparcOperand::CreateToken("%csr", S); 0
1132 break; 0
1133 case Sparc::CPQ: 0
1134 Op = SparcOperand::CreateToken("%cq", S); 0
1135 break; 0
1136 case Sparc::WIM: 0
1137 Op = SparcOperand::CreateToken("%wim", S); 0
1138 break; 0
1139 case Sparc::TBR: 0
1140 Op = SparcOperand::CreateToken("%tbr", S); 0
1141 break; 0
1142 case Sparc::PC: 0
1143 Op = SparcOperand::CreateToken("%pc", S); 0
1144 break; 0
1145 case Sparc::ICC: 0
1146 if (name == "xcc") 0
1147 Op = SparcOperand::CreateToken("%xcc", S); 0
1148 else ----
1149 Op = SparcOperand::CreateToken("%icc", S); 0
1150 break; 0
1151 } ----
1152 break; 0
1153 } ----
1154 if (matchSparcAsmModifiers(EVal, E)) { 0
1155 E = SMLoc::getFromPointer(Parser.getTok().getLoc().getPointer() - 1); 0
1156 Op = SparcOperand::CreateImm(EVal, S, E); 0
1157 } ----
1158 break; 0
1159 } ----
1160 ----
1161 case AsmToken::Plus: 0
1162 case AsmToken::Minus: ----
1163 case AsmToken::Integer: ----
1164 case AsmToken::LParen: ----
1165 case AsmToken::Dot: ----
1166 case AsmToken::Identifier: ----
1167 if (getParser().parseExpression(EVal, E)) 0
1168 break; 0
1169 ----
1170 int64_t Res; ----
1171 if (!EVal->evaluateAsAbsolute(Res)) { 0
1172 SparcMCExpr::VariantKind Kind = SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_13; 0
1173 ----
1174 if (getContext().getObjectFileInfo()->isPositionIndependent()) { 0
1175 if (isCall) 0
1176 Kind = SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_WPLT30; 0
1177 else ----
1178 Kind = SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_GOT13; 0
1179 } ----
1180 EVal = SparcMCExpr::create(Kind, EVal, getContext()); 0
1181 } ----
1182 Op = SparcOperand::CreateImm(EVal, S, E); 0
1183 break; 0
1184 } ----
1185 return (Op) ? MatchOperand_Success : MatchOperand_ParseFail; 0
1186 } ----
1187 ----
1188 OperandMatchResultTy ----
1189 SparcAsmParser::parseBranchModifiers(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
1190 // parse (,a|,pn|,pt)+ ----
1191 ----
1192 while (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Comma)) { 0
1193 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the comma 0
1194 ----
1195 if (!getLexer().is(AsmToken::Identifier)) 0
1196 return MatchOperand_ParseFail; 0
1197 StringRef modName = Parser.getTok().getString(); 0
1198 if (modName == "a" || modName == "pn" || modName == "pt") { 0

1455 // Determine if an expression contains a reference to the symbol ----
1456 // "_GLOBAL_OFFSET_TABLE_". ----
1457 static bool hasGOTReference(const MCExpr *Expr) { 0
1458 switch (Expr->getKind()) { 0
1459 case MCExpr::Target: 0
1460 if (const SparcMCExpr *SE = dyn_cast(Expr)) 0
1461 return hasGOTReference(SE->getSubExpr()); 0
1462 break; 0
1463 ----
1464 case MCExpr::Constant: 0
1465 break; 0
1466 ----
1467 case MCExpr::Binary: { 0
1468 const MCBinaryExpr *BE = cast(Expr); 0
1469 return hasGOTReference(BE->getLHS()) || hasGOTReference(BE->getRHS()); 0
1470 } ----
1471 ----
1472 case MCExpr::SymbolRef: { 0
1473 const MCSymbolRefExpr &SymRef = *cast(Expr); 0
1474 return (SymRef.getSymbol().getName() == "_GLOBAL_OFFSET_TABLE_"); 0
1475 } ----
1476 ----
1477 case MCExpr::Unary: 0
1478 return hasGOTReference(cast(Expr)->getSubExpr()); 0
1479 } ----
1480 return false; 0
1481 } ----

1483 const SparcMCExpr * ----
1484 SparcAsmParser::adjustPICRelocation(SparcMCExpr::VariantKind VK, 0
1485 const MCExpr *subExpr) { ----
1486 // When in PIC mode, "%lo(...)" and "%hi(...)" behave differently. ----
1487 // If the expression refers contains _GLOBAL_OFFSET_TABLE, it is ----
1488 // actually a %pc10 or %pc22 relocation. Otherwise, they are interpreted ----
1489 // as %got10 or %got22 relocation. ----
1490 ----
1491 if (getContext().getObjectFileInfo()->isPositionIndependent()) { 0
1492 switch(VK) { 0
1493 default: break; 0
1494 case SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_LO: 0
1495 VK = (hasGOTReference(subExpr) ? SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_PC10 0
1496 : SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_GOT10); ----
1497 break; 0
1498 case SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_HI: 0
1499 VK = (hasGOTReference(subExpr) ? SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_PC22 0
1500 : SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_GOT22); ----
1501 break; 0
1502 } ----
1503 } ----
1504 ----
1505 return SparcMCExpr::create(VK, subExpr, getContext()); 0
1506 } ----
1507 ----
1508 bool SparcAsmParser::matchSparcAsmModifiers(const MCExpr *&EVal, 0
1509 SMLoc &EndLoc) { ----
1510 AsmToken Tok = Parser.getTok(); 0
1511 if (!Tok.is(AsmToken::Identifier)) 0
1512 return false; 0
1513 ----
1514 StringRef name = Tok.getString(); 0
1515 ----
1516 SparcMCExpr::VariantKind VK = SparcMCExpr::parseVariantKind(name); 0
1517 switch (VK) { 0
1518 case SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_None: 0
1519 Error(getLoc(), "invalid operand modifier"); 0
1520 return false; 0
1521 ----
1522 case SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_GOTDATA_OP: 0
1523 case SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_TLS_GD_ADD: ----
1524 case SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_TLS_GD_CALL: ----
1525 case SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_TLS_IE_ADD: ----
1526 case SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_TLS_IE_LD: ----
1527 case SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_TLS_IE_LDX: ----
1528 case SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_TLS_LDM_ADD: ----
1529 case SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_TLS_LDM_CALL: ----
1530 case SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_TLS_LDO_ADD: ----
1531 // These are special-cased at tablegen level. ----
1532 return false; 0
1533 ----
1534 default: 0
1535 break; 0
1536 } ----
1537 ----
1538 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the identifier. 0
1539 if (Parser.getTok().getKind() != AsmToken::LParen) 0
1540 return false; 0
1541 ----
1542 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the LParen token. 0
1543 const MCExpr *subExpr; ----
1544 if (Parser.parseParenExpression(subExpr, EndLoc)) 0
1545 return false; 0
1546 ----
1547 EVal = adjustPICRelocation(VK, subExpr); 0
1548 return true; 0
1549 } 0

1561 unsigned SparcAsmParser::validateTargetOperandClass(MCParsedAsmOperand &GOp, 0
1562 unsigned Kind) { ----
1563 SparcOperand &Op = (SparcOperand &)GOp; 0
1564 if (Op.isFloatOrDoubleReg()) { 0
1565 switch (Kind) { 0
1566 default: break; 0
1567 case MCK_DFPRegs: 0
1568 if (!Op.isFloatReg() || SparcOperand::MorphToDoubleReg(Op)) 0
1569 return MCTargetAsmParser::Match_Success; 0
1570 break; 0
1571 case MCK_QFPRegs: 0
1572 if (SparcOperand::MorphToQuadReg(Op)) 0
1573 return MCTargetAsmParser::Match_Success; 0
1574 break; 0
1575 } ----
1576 } ----
1577 if (Op.isIntReg() && Kind == MCK_IntPair) { 0
1578 if (SparcOperand::MorphToIntPairReg(Op)) 0
1579 return MCTargetAsmParser::Match_Success; 0
1580 } ----
1581 if (Op.isCoprocReg() && Kind == MCK_CoprocPair) { 0
1582 if (SparcOperand::MorphToCoprocPairReg(Op)) 0
1583 return MCTargetAsmParser::Match_Success; 0
1584 } ----
1585 return Match_InvalidOperand; 0
1586 } ----

1457 static bool hasGOTReference(const MCExpr *Expr) { 1457 static bool hasGOTReference(const MCExpr *Expr) {

1459 case MCExpr::Target: 1459 case MCExpr::Target:

1461 return hasGOTReference(SE->getSubExpr()); 1461 return hasGOTReference(SE->getSubExpr());
1462 break; 1462 break;
1463 1463
1464 case MCExpr::Constant: 1464 case MCExpr::Constant:
1465 break; 1465 break;
1466 1466
1467 case MCExpr::Binary: { 1467 case MCExpr::Binary: {
1468 const MCBinaryExpr *BE = cast(Expr); 1468 const MCBinaryExpr *BE = cast(Expr);
1469 return hasGOTReference(BE->getLHS()) || hasGOTReference(BE->getRHS()); 1469 return hasGOTReference(BE->getLHS()) || hasGOTReference(BE->getRHS());
1470 } 1470 }
1471 1471
1472 case MCExpr::SymbolRef: { 1472 case MCExpr::SymbolRef: {

1474 return (SymRef.getSymbol().getName() == "_GLOBAL_OFFSET_TABLE_"); 1474 return (SymRef.getSymbol().getName() == "_GLOBAL_OFFSET_TABLE_");
1475 } 1475 }
1476 1476
1477 case MCExpr::Unary: 1477 case MCExpr::Unary:

1484 SparcAsmParser::adjustPICRelocation(SparcMCExpr::VariantKind VK, 1484 SparcAsmParser::adjustPICRelocation(SparcMCExpr::VariantKind VK,
1485 const MCExpr *subExpr) { 1485 const MCExpr *subExpr) {
1486 // When in PIC mode, "%lo(...)" and "%hi(...)" behave differently. 1486 // When in PIC mode, "%lo(...)" and "%hi(...)" behave differently.
1487 // If the expression refers contains _GLOBAL_OFFSET_TABLE, it is 1487 // If the expression refers contains _GLOBAL_OFFSET_TABLE, it is
1488 // actually a %pc10 or %pc22 relocation. Otherwise, they are interpreted 1488 // actually a %pc10 or %pc22 relocation. Otherwise, they are interpreted
1489 // as %got10 or %got22 relocation. 1489 // as %got10 or %got22 relocation.
1490 1490
1491 if (getContext().getObjectFileInfo()->isPositionIndependent()) { 1491 if (getContext().getObjectFileInfo()->isPositionIndependent()) {
1492 switch(VK) { 1492 switch(VK) {
1493 default: break; 1493 default: break;
1494 case SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_LO: 1494 case SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_LO:
1495 VK = (hasGOTReference(subExpr) ? SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_PC10 1495 VK = (hasGOTReference(subExpr) ? SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_PC10
1496 : SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_GOT10); 1496 : SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_GOT10);
1497 break; 1497 break;
1498 case SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_HI: 1498 case SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_HI:
1499 VK = (hasGOTReference(subExpr) ? SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_PC22 1499 VK = (hasGOTReference(subExpr) ? SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_PC22
1500 : SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_GOT22); 1500 : SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_GOT22);
1501 break; 1501 break;
1502 } 1502 }
1503 } 1503 }
1504 1504
1505 return SparcMCExpr::create(VK, subExpr, getContext()); 1505 return SparcMCExpr::create(VK, subExpr, getContext());
1506 } 1506 }
